---
import CaseStudyLayout from '../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro';
---

<CaseStudyLayout
  title="Sparks Grove — Delta Air Lines"
  description="How I led design for the Delta News Hub — a unified communications platform for the world's most-traveled airline, serving 90,000 employees and millions of customers."
  ogImage="/images/sparks-grove/news-hub.jpg"
>

<style>
  :root {
    --navy: #0B1B2B;
    --delta-red: #C8102E;
    --warm-white: #F7F5F2;
    --text-primary: #1A1A1A;
    --text-secondary: #5A5A5A;
    --text-light: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
    --accent: #C8102E;
  }

  /* ── Hero (full-bleed photo) ── */
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 100vh;
    min-height: 700px;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-end;
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .hero-bg img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center 40%;
  }

  .hero-bg::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
      to bottom,
      rgba(11,27,43,0.15) 0%,
      rgba(11,27,43,0.4) 50%,
      rgba(11,27,43,0.92) 100%
    );
  }

  .hero-content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 80px 80px;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .hero-label {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--delta-red);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5.5vw, 72px);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #fff;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--text-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  /* context-inner override (even columns for this page) */
  .context-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }

  /* ── Showcase ── */
  .showcase {
    background: var(--navy);
    padding: 120px 80px;
  }

  .showcase .section-heading { color: #fff; }
  .showcase .section-body { color: var(--text-light); }

  .showcase-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
    margin-top: 64px;
    max-width: 1400px;
  }

  .showcase-item {
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    transition: transform 0.4s ease, box-shadow 0.4s ease;
  }

  .showcase-item:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 24px 64px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }

  .showcase-item img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .showcase-caption {
    padding: 28px 32px;
  }

  .showcase-caption h3 {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .showcase-caption p {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
  }

  /* ── Two-up layout ── */
  .two-up {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
  }

  /* ── Full Bleed Image ── */
  .full-bleed { padding: 0; }

  .full-bleed img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 70vh;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  /* ── Event Section ── */
  .event-section {
    background: #111;
    padding: 120px 80px;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
    gap: 80px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .event-image {
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .event-image img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .event-text .section-heading { color: #fff; }
  .event-text .section-body { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero-content { padding: 0 32px 48px; }
    .event-section { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding: 80px 32px; }
    .showcase { padding: 80px 32px; }
    .two-up { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-bg">
      <img src="/images/sparks-grove/delta-777-right-inflight_new_livery.jpg" alt="Delta 777 in flight over the Rockies">
    </div>
    <div class="hero-content">
      <div class="hero-label">Sparks Grove &times; Delta Air Lines</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Reimagining Delta's Digital Storytelling</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">I led the design team that transformed how the world's most-traveled airline communicates with 90,000 employees and millions of customers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Context -->
  <section class="context">
    <div class="context-inner">
      <div>
        <div class="section-label">The Challenge</div>
        <h2 class="section-heading">A global airline needed a communications platform worthy of its brand.</h2>
        <p class="section-body">Delta's internal and external storytelling lived across fragmented, dated systems that didn't reflect the premium experience the airline had built in the air. I directed the design vision for the Delta News Hub — a unified communications platform that would serve corporate comms, media relations, and employee engagement under one cohesive experience.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="meta-grid">
          <div class="meta-item">
            <h4>My Role</h4>
            <p>UX Design Practice Leader</p>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-item">
            <h4>Agency</h4>
            <p>Sparks Grove</p>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-item">
            <h4>Scope</h4>
            <p>Web Platform, Content Strategy, Responsive Design</p>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-item">
            <h4>Team</h4>
            <p>UX Designers, Visual Designers, Content Strategists, Engineering</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Showcase: News Hub -->
  <div class="showcase">
    <div class="section-label">The Work</div>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Delta News Hub</h2>
    <p class="section-body">We designed a content-rich platform that balances editorial storytelling with real-time operational information — giving Delta a digital newsroom that felt as polished as their in-flight experience.</p>

    <div class="showcase-grid">
      <div class="showcase-item">
        <img src="/images/sparks-grove/news-hub.jpg" alt="Delta News Hub full homepage">
        <div class="showcase-caption">
          <h3>Homepage — Full Editorial System</h3>
          <p>Category-driven content architecture with featured stories, operational updates, and deep-dive sections.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="two-up">
        <div class="showcase-item">
          <img src="/images/sparks-grove/DNH01.jpg" alt="Delta News Hub header and navigation">
          <div class="showcase-caption">
            <h3>Navigation & Information Architecture</h3>
            <p>Clean content hierarchy organized by audience and topic.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="showcase-item">
          <img src="/images/sparks-grove/delta-4.jpg" alt="Delta News Hub responsive views">
          <div class="showcase-caption">
            <h3>Responsive & Mobile Experience</h3>
            <p>Adaptive layouts that maintained editorial quality across every device.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Event / Centennial -->
  <div class="event-section">
    <div class="event-image">
      <img src="/images/sparks-grove/gala_5.jpg" alt="Delta centennial celebration with illuminated aircraft">
    </div>
    <div class="event-text">
      <div class="section-label">Beyond Digital</div>
      <h2 class="section-heading">The work extended into brand moments that mattered.</h2>
      <p class="section-body">Our relationship with Delta went deeper than screens. The design language we established informed brand experiences across the organization — from centennial celebrations to employee engagement campaigns. When you lead design for a brand this iconic, every touchpoint has to earn its place.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Full Bleed Closing -->
  <section class="full-bleed">
    <img src="/images/sparks-grove/20150925_a330a2a_stills_cam1-1179-v2.jpg.jpeg" alt="Delta A330 over the ocean">
  </section>

</CaseStudyLayout>
